  "text": "where r 1 is the coordinate distance to the center of the BH c BH , and the width w is chosen as half the coordinate distance between the two compact objects. This choice ensures that close to the BH, the metric is nearly γ KS ij , while away from the hole, we recover conformal flatness and maximal slicing. The introduction of the exponential damping e −(r1/w) 4 is the most important difference between the choices of conformal metric and extrinsic curvature in [CITATION_1] and [19] . That change is indeed necessary to avoid large deviations from equilibrium.",
